      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UNLEASH SHIRLEY (2) has a strong record here with two wins and a minor from six starts. Was out of placings last time (30.43) at The Gardens in a Grade 3/4, finishing fourth and beaten 12 lengths. Looks suited and should go close. SUDDEN SURPRISE (6) was a little disappointing last start at The Gardens when 4th (23.06) over 400m. Has never missed the frame here at the trip including one win. Worth another chance. NOVA LASS (1) found trouble in the run at this course and distance last time and fell. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Has the ability and can measure up. AVIATION (7) was in the money last start and poses a threat again.",
